# Web App (Next.js Frontend) Rules

## Architecture
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- Apollo Client for GraphQL
- Clerk authentication
- Tailwind CSS for styling

## Development Commands
```bash
pnpm dev         # Start development server
pnpm build       # Build the application
pnpm start       # Start production server
pnpm lint        # Lint the code
pnpm check:types # Type check
pnpm test        # Run tests
pnpm codegen     # Generate GraphQL types
```

## Styling & UI
- Use `@repo/ui` components exclusively
- Use Tailwind classes from shadcn theme
- No custom CSS files (use Tailwind utilities)
- Follow responsive design patterns
- Use proper color variables from theme

## GraphQL & Data Fetching
- Use Apollo Client for GraphQL operations
- Create `.gql` files for queries/mutations
- Use generated types from codegen
- Implement proper loading and error states
- Use Apollo cache effectively

## Component Architecture
- Use React Server Components where appropriate
- Client components only when needed
- Proper component composition
- Use custom hooks for logic
- Follow existing patterns in modules/

## Routing & Navigation
- Use Next.js App Router conventions
- Implement proper page layouts
- Use middleware for auth checks
- Follow existing route structure

## Authentication
- Clerk integration for auth flows
- Protect routes with middleware
- Use auth context appropriately
- Handle auth states properly

## File Organization
- Group by feature in `modules/`
- Separate components, hooks, and utils
- Use index files for exports
- Follow kebab-case for file names

## Performance
- Optimize images and assets
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement code splitting
- Optimize bundle size
- Use Next.js performance features

## Testing
- Use Vitest for component testing
- Test user interactions
- Mock GraphQL operations
- Maintain test coverage

## Type Safety
- Use generated GraphQL types
- Proper TypeScript configurations
- No `any` types
- Use strict type checking